        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 11:21AM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 1121 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
over Boone Hall Plantation, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...The combination of gusty winds and saturated ground could
knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant, Daniel Island, Isle Of Palms, Sullivan's Island,
Awendaw, Mount Pleasant Regional Airport, Boone Hall Plantation,
Mount Pleasant Towne Centre, Capers Inlet and Cainhoy.

This includes I-526 between mile markers 27 and 31.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
